    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>beef strips</strong> to a small bowl with your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and set aside to marinate</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-beef-stir-fry-with-pickled-radish-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>radishes</strong> (as finely as you can)</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced radishes</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and set aside \u2013 these are your<strong> pickled radishes</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-beef-stir-fry-with-pickled-radish-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-beef-stir-fry-with-pickled-radish-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong> finely</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Dissolve 1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span><strong> Knorr beef stock cube </strong>in 120ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-beef-stir-fry-with-pickled-radish-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over the highest heat</p><p>Once your pan is very hot, add the <strong>beef strips</strong> and cook for 1 min exactly, to sear the outside, but prevent them from overcooking</p><p>Tip: You'll finish cooking these in the sauce later</p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>beef strips</strong> to a plate to rest</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-beef-stir-fry-with-pickled-radish-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (there should be some juices leftover from the beef strips), add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>apple[s]</strong> (skin on)</p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>grated apple </strong>then your<strong> mirin </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until the apple starts to break down</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-beef-stir-fry-with-pickled-radish-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> stock</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until the sauce has thickened a little</p><p>Stir through the <strong>rested beef strips</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-beef-stir-fry-with-pickled-radish-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Korean beef stir-fry</strong> with the<strong> cooked cauliflower rice</strong> to the side and the <strong>pickled radishes</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong> over the top of the stir-fry</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
